article.headline: Oregon St. 65, CS Bakersfield 59
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. -- Roeland Schaftenaar had 20 points and eight rebounds Monday in Oregon State's 65-59 nonconference win over Cal State Bakersfield. Oregon State (9-10) used a 7-0 run early in the second half to break a 34-34 tie and take the lead for good. But the Beavers had to hold on late as the Roadrunners cut a 13-point deficit to four in the final minute. Alex Johnson had 19 points -- including six 3-pointers -- to lead Cal State Bakersfield (5-15). Schaftenaar, the Pac-10 Conference's player of the week after Oregon State's surprising wins at California and Stanford, was 9-of-15 from the floor and also had three assists and two blocks. Calvin Haynes added 19 points and five rebounds for the Beavers.
